OL,7,F"Patient safety is of course the
OL,8,Fnumber one priority. Health leaders
OL,9,Fand their teams will pull out all the
OL,10,Fstops to fill rotas ahead of the
OL,11,Fstrikes, but the reality is more
OL,12,Fpatients having their operations or
OL,13,Fappointments cancelled, which will
OL,14,Fimpact on attempts to tackle waiting
OL,15,Flists for routine hospital care.
OL,17,F"As always, it is patients who bear
OL,18,Fthe greatest burden from industrial
OL,19,Faction."
